          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Marinate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the marinade in a bowl. Use {{plain-yoghurt}} of yoghurt, the juice of {{lemon}} lemon, {{garlic}} of grated garlic, and {{olive-oil}} of olive oil. Add the spices: {{cumin-ground}} of cumin, {{coriander-ground}} of coriander, {{allspice}} of allspice, {{paprika-smoked}} of smoked paprika, {{turmeric}} of turmeric, and {{cinnamon-ground}} of cinnamon. Season with {{sea-salt-fine}} of salt and {{black-pepper}} of pepper. Add {{chicken-thigh}} chicken thighs and coat them well. Cover and chill overnight, or at least 4 hours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roast and slice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C. Arrange the chicken on a baking tray in a single layer. Roast for 30 to 35 minutes until deeply charred at the edges and cooked through. Rest for 5 minutes, then slice thinly. Load into warm pitta with garlic yoghurt, tomato, fresh herbs and pickled chilli.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Troubleshooting",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": null,
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Use a large tray so thighs have space. At 220°C they should char at the edges in 30 minutes; if the oven is slower, switch to the grill for the last 5 minutes.",
              "cause": "Crowded tray, or oven not hot enough.",
              "symptom": "Pale, steamed-looking chicken with no char"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Thighs are the correct cut; they stay moist at high heat. Check the internal temperature: 74°C is cooked through.",
              "cause": "Overcooked, or used breast meat.",
              "symptom": "Dry chicken"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Score the skin deeply with a knife before marinating; this allows the spices to reach the meat. Overnight is reliably better than a short marinade.",
              "cause": "Less than 4 hours marinating.",
              "symptom": "Marinade not penetrating"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "Common problems"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shawarma is the street food of the Levant from Istanbul to Tel Aviv to Beirut: stacked meat on a rotating spit, shaved to order into flatbreads with pickles, sauces and fresh herbs. The spit is not available at home, but the marinade and high oven come close to the result. It is a Friday night dinner that produces excellent leftovers for the next day's lunch.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
